        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 12:29PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1228 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Barr to 7 miles southeast of Batesville to near
Holcomb. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Charleston, Waterford, Enid, Paynes, Crossroad, Tyro, Oakland, Como,
Chulahoma, Glenville, Harmontown, Gums, Rosebloom, Bluff, Bryant,
Teckville, George Payne State Park, Taylor, Wyatte, and Cascilla.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM CDT for
northeastern and northwestern Mississippi.</instruction>
